On Sun, Sep 23, 2012 at 4:59 PM, courtney hook <courtneyhook(-at-)shaw.ca> wrote:
> Just a quick heads up on this wheel cylinder. My OEM cylinder decided to
puke a half reservoir of brake fluid all over the place, so I dutifully went
into my parts stash and found I had two replacements from KMM (generic
importer, who knows where these were made). It looked very well made, but when
it came time to mount it to the backing plate, I went through my complete
repertoire of mechanics language, and was moving on to navy language before I
finally realized that the threaded mounting hole for the wheel cylinder was
off by about 1/16". This was enough to prevent me from threading the bolt in.
I was finally forced to oval the mounting hole in the backing plate the 1/16"
to get it to mount up. NOT impressed. Not the best thing to do, but since it's
Sunday, and the locals just look at me and drool with vacant questioning eyes,
I was forced to improvise. So there's your heads up on this product. Maybe I
just got a bad one.
> Courtney
